history.content:
16A discussions are non-binding commitments so you can choose whichever time slot works best (to be released after the first class)

16A lab slots you'll have to choose now, try not to miss lab but if you have to, there's buffer lab times

61A discussion/lab in the past you choose in the beginning of the semester (but technically you can go to other disc/lab if you ask them and they're not too crowded)

Career fairs are usually in the noon/afternoon - sometimes you'll just have to skip class for these

Hi. I’m taking EE 16A and CS 61A this upcoming semester. What’s the best time for 61A and 16A labs and 16A discussions? I wanna account for extracurricular activities along with career fairs. I picked the Friday 5-8pm lab section for 16A, so I can use my morning energy and willpower for intensive tasks. I’m not sure if it conflicts with any kind of CS activities. Please inform me.
